{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":875,"record_hash":"sha256:bdef633ef651ca6a09f85b5ada3882322cdc47b829da3ce3cf153acdfbb3dc70","timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:35:21.052Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Review synthesis is back. The strongest overlap from the subagents is that the implementation is close, but a few fixes are worth doing before this is merge-ready.\n\n::code-comment{title=\"[P1] Dry-run creates GitMeta state\" body=\"`Session::open(repo_path)` runs before the dry-run branch, and GitMeta creates/migrates `.git/git-meta.sqlite` on open. That violates the POC contract that `--dry-run` performs no GitMeta writes. Dry-run needs a non-creating read path, or it should treat missing GitMeta state as empty before opening a writable session.\" file=\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\" start=44 end=59 priority=1 confidence=0.95}\n\n::code-comment{title=\"[P2] Deduplicate duplicate records within one capture\" body=\"The write plan checks records only against persisted hash sets, not hashes already selected during this run. A transcript containing the same trimmed JSONL record twice will overcount `recordsNew` and append duplicate transcript envelopes. Clone the hash sets into mutable planned sets and insert as each record is accepted.\" file=\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\" start=105 end=118 priority=2 confidence=0.9}\n\n::code-comment{title=\"[P2] Transcript append can duplicate after partial failure\" body=\"The transcript envelope is appended before `transcript-record-hashes` is updated. If capture exits or `set_add` fails after `list_push`, a later capture can append the same envelope again. Either make the list/hash update atomic through GitMeta if possible, or rebuild transcript hashes from existing envelope records before planning appends.\" file=\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/gitmeta.rs\" start=64 end=77 priority=2 confidence=0.82}\n\n::code-comment{title=\"[P2] Path identity uses lossy UTF-8\" body=\"The canonical transcript path is converted with `to_string_lossy()` and then used as the fallback session-key hash input. Distinct non-UTF-8 paths can collapse to the same replacement-character string. Hash platform-native path bytes for identity, and use lossy text only for storage/display if needed.\" file=\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/capture.rs\" start=107 end=108 priority=2 confidence=0.8}\n\n::code-comment{title=\"[P2] `--status-after` is accepted but ignored\" body=\"The global `--status-after` flag is accepted for `agent-session capture`, but this command returns a bare capture report instead of the CLI's documented `{ result, status }` JSON wrapper for mutation commands. Either wire the normal status-after path or explicitly reject/status-disable it for this hidden command.\" file=\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs\" start=270 end=280 priority=2 confidence=0.84}\n\n::code-comment{title=\"[P3] Preserve `payload.type` in event kind\" body=\"The POC contract says event kind should use top-level `type` plus `payload.type` when present, but normalization currently stores only top-level `type`. Include `payload.type` for records such as `event_msg` while preserving the existing fallback.\" file=\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-capture/src/transcript.rs\" start=94 end=95 priority=3 confidence=0.78}\n\n::code-comment{title=\"[P3] `--include-transcript` help omits local-only storage warning\" body=\"The help text warns that transcripts can contain sensitive data, but the contract also requires warning that POC storage is local-only. Add that sentence to the option help.\" file=\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/args/agent_session.rs\" start=22 end=24 priority=3 confidence=0.94}\n\nAlso worth noting, but less clear-cut: the pinned `git-meta-lib` dependency pulls a second Gitoxide stack (`gix 0.81`) alongside GitButler’s workspace `gix 0.83`. That matches the current spec choice to use the GitHub rev, but it is a real build-size/compile-time risk.\n\nI’d fix the P1/P2 items first, then the two small P3 contract nits. The shell-output and metrics comments were more policy/preferences than bugs, especially since the plan explicitly said shell should use the same contract phrases.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T11:35:21.052Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}